1
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:26,220
Welcome to a large-scale
life simulation game.

2
00:00:26,980 --> 00:00:33,140
Welcome to The Truth, a large-scale
open-world social deduction game.

3
00:00:33,140 --> 00:00:36,020
As a player, you will enter
different dungeon worlds

4
00:00:36,020 --> 00:00:38,740
and embark on your own adventure.

5
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:41,480
This game features four dungeon worlds.

6
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:43,720
(Dungeon 1, 2, 3, 4)
In each dungeon,

7
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:45,800
(Role)
you will unlock a new identity,

8
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,920
experience a different life,

9
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:49,680
meet the NPCs within,

10
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:51,760
explore and interact

11
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:54,880
with each dungeon's unique story,

12
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:56,000
solve its mysteries,

13
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,480
and expose the true culprit.

14
00:00:57,480 --> 00:00:59,200
(Dungeon 1, 2, 3, 4 Cleared)
Clear all four dungeons

15
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,160
to earn the completion achievement

16
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:02,800
(Completion Achievement)
and unlock the hidden ending.

17
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:04,480
Each dungeon

18
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,600
(Case 1, Case 2)
may contain

19
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:07,160
one or more cases.

20
00:01:07,160 --> 00:01:08,400
(Random, Detectives, Suspects)
When a case begins,

21
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:10,400
players will be randomly assigned

22
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,360
as either detectives or suspects.

23
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:14,160
(Suspects, NPC)
The true culprit could be hiding

24
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:15,520
among the suspect players or the NPCs.

25
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:17,400
(True Culprit)
Look carefully.

26
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:19,240
The true culprit's objective

27
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:20,720
is to stay hidden.

28
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:23,400
(True Culprit)
Only the true culprit is allowed to lie.

29
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:24,760
(Main Quest, Investigation, Exploration, Rewards)
As a case unfolds,

30
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:27,200
(Skill Cards, Trial, Stamina Points, Side Quests)
players can

31
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:28,800
use game mechanics
to advance the investigation.

32
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:30,800
Use them wisely,

33
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,400
and you may uncover
an unexpected breakthrough.

34
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:34,800
(Suspects, True Culprit, NPCs)
When the case ends,

35
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,520
it'll be time to vote
for the true culprit.

36
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:38,680
If the culprit is identified,

37
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:40,120
(Correct Vote, True Culprit)
players who voted correctly

38
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,200
will receive a Golden Key.

39
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,840
If the true culprit

40
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,680
(True Culprit, Player)
receives fewer votes than the others,

41
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:48,200
(True Culprit, Votes, Player)
he will also earn a Golden Key.

42
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:50,960
(Player)
Golden Keys will be tallied

43
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:52,560
at the end and exchanged

44
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,920
(Skill Cards) for Skill Cards.

45
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,860
(Gentle Reminder)
Please note:

46
00:01:56,860 --> 00:01:58,840
(All characters and details
are fictional) The Game Guide

47
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:00,650
(All acts and scenes are fictional)
is loading.

48
00:02:00,650 --> 00:02:02,690
(All content used in this program)
Immerse yourselves in the experience.

49
00:02:02,690 --> 00:02:04,010
(has had consent given)
Begin the investigation!

50
00:02:04,010 --> 00:02:04,340
(Appropriate safety measures were taken
Please do not imitate)

51
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:04,780
(Minors should watch
under adult supervision)

52
00:02:04,780 --> 00:02:05,860
(LOADING)

53
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:10,700
(LOADING...)

54
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:13,220
(Dungeon Pass)

55
00:02:18,060 --> 00:02:19,380
(THE TRUTH)

56
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:24,460
=The Truth=

57
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:49,600
Is anyone there?

58
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,200
Is anyone there?

59
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,680
Is anyone there?

60
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:03,640
Yeah.

61
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:05,440
Who's there?

62
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:08,000
Ke Stubborn, are you here too?

63
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:10,560
Yeah. You're Yang Glory, aren't you?

64
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,280
That's right.

65
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:13,200
What happened?

66
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,120
Why are we...

67
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:15,320
I don't know.

68
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:17,880
Where... is this?

69
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,520
I don't know.

70
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,280
How did we end up here

71
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,040
the moment we opened our eyes?

72
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,720
Weren't we dead?

73
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,680
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

74
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,600
Come on, everyone. Cheers!

75
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,160
Drink this toast,

76
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,240
and we'll meet again in the next life.

77
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:35,480
Yeah.

78
00:03:35,660 --> 00:03:38,180
(What happened to these two?)

79
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,000
This...

80
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,820
(The door won't open)
Is anyone there?

81
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,680
Is anyone there?

82
00:03:43,280 --> 00:03:44,160
Help!

83
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:45,500
Help!

84
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:47,020
(Who's calling for help?)
Wait!

85
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:47,960
Wait!

86
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:48,620
Help!

87
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:50,960
Did you hear that?

88
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:52,280
Let us out!

89
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:52,960
Come on, let's check it out.

90
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:54,160
Let's go.

91
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,320
Where is it?

92
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:56,640
In here.

93
00:03:58,880 --> 00:03:59,360
Is anyone there?

94
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,440
Help!

95
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:06,960
Help!

96
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:09,600
Hurry! Let us out!

97
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:11,080
How did you get trapped in there?

98
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:11,520
You guys...

99
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,560
What's going on?

100
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,560
It opened just like that?

101
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:17,830
Yeah.

102
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:19,270
It opened just like that.

103
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,240
You couldn't get it open?

104
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,420
(Seriously?)

105
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:23,840
(Yang looks at you in disappointment.)

106
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:25,800
We couldn't push it open, Sister.

107
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,400
So you're "Tui Bukai".

108
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:28,800
Who are you?

109
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:29,600
(Anyone surnamed Tui is dangerous.)

110
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,640
His name is "Tui Budong".

111
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,480
(Double kill incoming.)
We can't open it from the inside.

112
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,920
Who are you?

113
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:35,800
I'm Ke.

114
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,080
Ke Stubborn.

115
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:38,840
Who?

116
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,080
Don't you know me?

117
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:41,680
No.

118
00:04:42,180 --> 00:04:47,420
(None of the four recognize them.)

119
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,280
I'm

120
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:48,920
Yang Glory.

121
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:51,480
(Yang Glory played by Yang Chaoyue)
I'm the little cook from Truth Inn.

122
00:04:53,140 --> 00:04:54,540
(Why doesn't anyone recognize
Ke Stubborn and Yang Glory?)

123
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,600
Thousand-Faced Eagle King.

124
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,480
Yeah.

125
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,520
You don't know us?

126
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:58,680
What are they talking about?

127
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,600
His name is Ning Waver.

128
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,560
His name is Ding Pillar.

129
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:06,160
His name is He Ha.

130
00:05:06,160 --> 00:05:06,400
Yeah.

131
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:06,880
And you...

132
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,160
Jin Thrifty.

133
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:09,520
That night,

134
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:11,240
we all raised our glasses

135
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:12,880
and shared a drink.

136
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:16,040
After we finished that toast,
we sent Ning Waver on his way.

137
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:16,320
Yeah.

138
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:20,020
(Ning Waver is dead.)

139
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:20,840
And after

140
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,200
taking that medicine,

141
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,960
a few days later, we died too.

142
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,160
We even asked you

143
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:26,840
to bury us together

144
00:05:26,840 --> 00:05:27,760
with Ning Waver.

145
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,800
Yeah.

146
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:29,440
What?

147
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:31,620
(Yang Glory, Ke Stubborn,
Ding Pillar, and He Ha are dead too?)

148
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,360
Don't you remember?

149
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,360
Wait a second.

150
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:36,000
My name

151
00:05:36,880 --> 00:05:38,120
is

152
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,360
"Jin Da".

153
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:41,360
(Jin Thrifty)
without the "Thrifty".

154
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:44,660
(Something is way off.)

155
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:46,240
I may not be a princess,

156
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:48,360
but I do look like one.

157
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:49,800
(Self-proclaimed princess.)
I'm the treasure restorer

158
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,520
(Jin Da, Treasure Restorer)
at this exhibition hall.

159
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,320
My theme song is...

160
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:56,760
(Her urge to perform strikes again.)
♪Baby, I'm sorry♪

161
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,440
♪I didn't mean it♪

162
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,280
What's she singing?

163
00:05:59,280 --> 00:05:59,800
No idea.

164
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,760
(A masterpiece without an audience.)

165
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,880
♪Hurry up♪

166
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:05,360
(Playing the lute to a cow.)
♪Come restore it♪

167
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,520
That's my song.

168
00:06:06,860 --> 00:06:08,200
(Works for me.)

169
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,560
I'm "Ding Tian".

170
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,760
Without "Pillar".

171
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:12,080
(Tui Exhibition Hall)

172
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,760
I'm a security guard

173
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,000
(Ding Tian Security Guard)
here.

174
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:16,200
You're Ning Waver,

175
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,000
Young Commander.

176
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,120
No.

177
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,400
I'm

178
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:20,930
"Ningbo".

179
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:22,560
As in Wuhan Ningbo.

180
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:25,520
I'm also a new security guard.

181
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:27,180
(Tui Exhibition Hall)

182
00:06:27,180 --> 00:06:29,180
(Ningbo, New Security Guard)

183
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,920
Then his name can't be

184
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:31,960
"Hehe", right?

185
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,000
(Hehe)

186
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,320
My name is Hehe.

187
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:35,680
(Tui Exhibition Hall)

188
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:37,100
I'm also a security guard here.

189
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:37,900
(Hehe Security Guard)

190
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,240
No, that's not right.

191
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:42,440
We're here today

192
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:45,520
(Jin Jing as Jin Da)
to attend the "Detective Maniac" exhibition.

193
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:47,520
(They came here for the exhibition)
That's why we're wearing these outfits.

194
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:48,200
That's right.

195
00:06:48,930 --> 00:06:50,440
(Zhou Keyu as Ke Stubborn)
Wait, what exhibition?

196
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:53,960
Today, we only have a theme.

197
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:56,120
We're just cosplaying.

198
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:57,300
(She doesn't know what cosplaying is)

199
00:06:57,740 --> 00:06:58,560
(Never heard of it)

200
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:58,960
No.

201
00:06:59,520 --> 00:07:00,920
Cosplaying? What do you mean?

202
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,400
Do you know what era this is?

203
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,000
Year 260.

204
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,760
It's the year 2026.

205
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:10,460
(Tui Year 2026, May 29)

206
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:13,820
(Year 260 of Tui)

207
00:07:23,460 --> 00:07:25,340
(Tui Year 2026)

208
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:29,580
(Tui Exhibition Hall)

209
00:07:30,140 --> 00:07:31,520
(Why did people from Year 260
of Tui appear in Year 2026?)

210
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:32,280
No.

211
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,680
I know you might think

212
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,840
we are crazy right now.

213
00:07:34,840 --> 00:07:35,480
Yes.

214
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:38,560
But every word I'm saying is true.

215
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,720
The four of you

216
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:41,080
definitely have a problem.

217
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,480
Have a problem?

218
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,560
Something is wrong with you all.

219
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,560
You came in being so offensive.

220
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,960
First, you said we were dead.

221
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,520
Then you said something
was wrong with us.

222
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:51,480
(Liu Yuning as Ningbo)
And you said you were buried together.

223
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,960
And that you sent me away.
Where did I go?

224
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,360
You're really ominous.

225
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,760
I mean no offense.

226
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:56,160
Sister,

227
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:58,520
don't you remember what happened
between us in our past lives?

228
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,400
Who are you?

229
00:07:59,400 --> 00:07:59,960
Go away.

230
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:16,240
Wait.

231
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,520
This thing kept flashing just now.

232
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:18,680
What does this mean?

233
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:20,320
The red light flashed
several times just now,

234
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:22,280
and it made a creaking sound.

235
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,200
Can someone explain this?

236
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:23,720
Okay.

237
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:25,280
Do you know

238
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,080
there are legends

239
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:27,800
about ghost soldiers.

240
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:30,120
(The legend exists in Tui Year 2026)
Do you know?

241
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,920
There are ghost soldiers here.

242
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,670
There are legends
about ghost soldiers here.

243
00:08:33,670 --> 00:08:34,400
That's ridiculous.

244
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,240
Impossible.

245
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:36,120
It's not a joke.

246
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:37,700
(Zhang Linghe as Hehe)

247
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:39,030
Things haven't been
peaceful lately either.

248
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:40,550
Because of the legend,

249
00:08:40,550 --> 00:08:41,670
many villagers

250
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:43,120
have disappeared.

251
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,000
(Some villagers recently disappeared
because of the rumors)

252
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,160
Do you know what sound was that?

253
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,000
What?

254
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,520
The sound of the Ghost Armor.

255
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,960
Ghost Armor?

256
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,320
(The sound just now
came from the Ghost Armor)

257
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:54,160
The Ghost Armor can
control people's minds.

258
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:55,520
The Ghost Armor can
control people's minds.

259
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:57,080
Because this Ghost Armor

260
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,920
has been stained
with ghost soldier blood.

261
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:01,000
If you get too close to it,

262
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:01,720
you will be controlled.

263
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:04,440
Its smell will affect your mind.

264
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:08,140
(The Ghost Armor controls
people's minds through smell)

265
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:08,760
Okay.

266
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:10,400
I'll take you to see the Ghost Armor.

267
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:11,440
Follow me closely.

268
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:13,120
You two ancient people, stand here.

269
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:16,000
Take a look
and tell us what year this is.

270
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,160
Three, two, one.

271
00:09:21,180 --> 00:09:23,140
(New scene unlocked: Tui
Exhibition Hall's first-floor corridor)

272
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,980
(Displaying modern objects)
Look at this.

273
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,320
Isn't this just a smooth stone?

274
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:30,640
Everyone, do you know what this is?

275
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:31,640
Sorcery.

276
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:32,700
(They have never seen
such advanced technology)

277
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:34,360
